@@TJvWizardRouteMapList.IncludeDisabled
Summary
  Specifies if disabled pages are included in the list.
Description
  Use IncludeDisabled to specify whether disabled pages are included in the list or not. If
  IncludeDisabled is true, the disabled pages are shown as well but they are drawn using a disabled
  look and the items aren't clickable and won't hot track.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvWizardRouteMapList.ItemColor
Summary
  Sets the background color for the items in the list.
Description
  Use ItemColor to specify the background color of the items in the list.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvWizardRouteMapList.ItemHeight
Summary
  Sets the height of the items in the list.
Description
  Use ItemHeight to specify the height in pixels of the items in the list.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvWizardRouteMapList.ItemText
Summary
  Specifies the text to display in the items.
Description
  Use ItemText to specify the text to display in the items. Depending on the value of ItemText, the
  control displays either the Page's Caption, Header.Title, Header.SubTitle or no text at all.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvWizardRouteMapList.OnDrawItem
Summary
  Occurs when an item should be drawn.
Description
  Write a handler for this event to custom draw the items in the list. You can also use this event if
  you only need to change the attributes of the Canvas. For example, you can change the Canvas's Font,
  Brush and Pen properties to modify the colors and fonts used by the default drawing code.
Parameters
  Sender      - The control that triggered the event.
  ACanvas     - The canvas to draw on.
  ARect       - The rect area to draw in.
  MousePos    - The position of the mouse in client coordinates.
  PageIndex   - The index of the active page.
  DefaultDraw - Set to true to perform default drawing, false otherwise.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvWizardRouteMapList.Rounded
Summary
  Specifies whether items are drawn with rounded or straight corners.
Description
  Use Rounded to specify whether the items background are drawn as a rounded or straight edged
  rectangle. If Rounded is true, the control uses RoundRect to draw the item's background otherwise it
  uses Rectangle.
See Also
  RoundRect, Rectangle

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvWizardRouteMapList.ShowImages
Summary
  Specifies whether the items displays images.
Description
  Use ShowImages to specify whether the items display images or not. The images are taken from the
  HeaderImages property of the associated TJvWizard.
See Also
  TJvWizard.HeaderImages

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvWizardRouteMapList.TextOffset
Summary
  Specifies the offset of the text in the items.
Description
  Use TextOffset to specify the offset in pixels of the text in each item. TextOffset is interpreted
  according to the value of Alignment. For example, if Alignment is taLeftJustify, TextOffset is
  calculated from the item's left edge. If Alignment is taRightJustify, TextOffset is calculated from
  the right edge. If Alignment is taCenter, TextOffset is calculated from the top and the text is
  horizontally centered.
See Also
  TJvWizardRouteMapList.HorzOffset, TJvWizardRouteMapList.VertOffset

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvWizardRouteMapList.TextOnly
Summary
  Controls the painting of images and buttons.
Description
  Use TextOnly to get a simple text list instead of a button list.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvWizardRouteMapList.VertOffset
Summary
  Specifies the offset from the top of the first item in the list.
Description
  Use VertOffset to specify the offset in pixels from the top edge of the items in the list.
See Also
  TJvWizardRouteMapList.HorzOffset, TJvWizardRouteMapList.TextOffset

